Review text: My first issue with this product was that the photos lead you to believe you are ordering a regular size balance beam. Upon arrival I noticed a short box but thought nothing of it. I figured the box contained two pieces that connected to form a full beam. Unfortunately, when my niece opened her gift the box only contained one 4 foot piece. I was scratching my head. Minutes later I fired up the amazon app and bought another to complete the full 8’ beam. The second package arrived 2 days later. My niece was excited. I wasn’t thrilled because the first 4 footer had a blue bottom and the second one arrived with a purple bottom. This wasn’t a huge deal but I was annoyed because no color options were provided. We put the pieces together. Each piece fits together with a Velcro flap. I got over the color mismatch but I was annoyed because the two pieces didn’t fit together seamlessly. It had a gap. I think this is due to low quality control. Amazon exchanged one half to hopefully remove the unsafe middle gap. It’s a balance beam and a gap in the middle is an injury waiting to happen. Furthermore, the plastic bottoms do not have grips so the beam will slide on wood floors. In short, the product is crap. I should have known better because if you look closely at the beams in the stock photos look like junk.

Review text: The media could not be loaded.                , 'xa0I am very impressed with this balance beam! I got it for our 3-year-old daughter who is in gymnastics class but wouldn’t even walk across a beam without assistance from the teacher. We currently have it on the lowest setting to the floor and on carpet and it’s VERY sturdy, no wobbling AT ALL. The day after we received this, my daughter went to gymnastics class and did ice cream scoop walks across a raised balance beam ALL BY HERSELF. I was SO proud. Literally, one day after we set this up for her at home, she is already showing so much progress. Very happy I got this beam for her!

It really needs some detachable feet that come out far enough to keep it steady."

Review text: "Great beam for a beginner to intermediate gymnast. Not sure how well it would handle someone with advanced skills due to the foam core. It is nice and sturdy doesnt flex or give when you walk or tumble. We have used it for a week straight every day so fair so good. I have had an adult working skills and basic tumble no problem. One thing I wish they could fix and why I didnt give 5 stars, is because of the way it folds. It should have Velcro on the middle where it folds. So when the two pieces touch it becomes more sturdy and finds itself in a straight line. Because of th fold, when you flip it out straight it flexes to the left or right and doesnt lay directly in a straight line. If your tumbling is off a hair it moves the beam offset on one end or the other. I like the material. Its light weight and is a great asset for practice at home or fearful students in the gym. I am a gymnastics instructor and believe its worth the buy due to the thick core and relative sturdiness to it. My only real comparison is a wood floor beam and a foam beam (that feels like the material of a pool noodle.) So in comparison this is a great place to start."

The Springee beam is perfect for beginners and the fabric is nice, it’s soft and seems durable.

The kids love it.

The problem is the “soft hinge”.

It seems flimsy to me, well made as far as materials and stitching but overall, I’m disappointed.

Review text: "Great beam for a beginner to intermediate gymnast. Not sure how well it would handle someone with advanced skills due to the foam core. One thing I wish they could fix and why I didnt give 5 stars, is because of the way it folds. It should have Velcro on the middle where it folds. Because of th fold, when you flip it out straight it flexes to the left or right and doesnt lay directly in a straight line. If your tumbling is off a hair it moves the beam offset on one end or the other. I like the material. Its light weight and is a great asset for practice at home or fearful students in the gym. I am a gymnastics instructor and believe its worth the buy due to the thick core and relative sturdiness to it. My only real comparison is a wood floor beam and a foam beam (that feels like the material of a pool noodle.) So in comparison this is a great place to start."

Review text:
The Springee beam is perfect for beginners and the fabric is nice, it’s soft and seems durable.

The kids love it.

The problem is the “soft hinge”.

It is not solid enough and allows for movement and bending mid beam.

So the beam is not straight, unless constantly adjusted.

The grippy bottom is decent on carpet but can easily be slid across the tile when there is no weight on it.

It seems flimsy to me, well made as far as materials and stitching but overall, I’m disappointed.

The beam is perfect and my daughter loves it!  

Within 30 minutes on Christmas morning she was landing back walk overs and back handsprings, something she wouldn’t even try on her old beam that was 6-12” in the air.  

This will give her the practice and confidence she needs for the gym.

It doesn’t budge an inch on top of her mats because of the gripper dots on the bottom.  

I would recommend this beam!

Minutes later I fired up the amazon app and bought another to complete the full 8’ beam. The second package arrived 2 days later. My niece was excited. I wasn’t thrilled because the first 4 footer had a blue bottom and the second one arrived with a purple bottom. This wasn’t a huge deal but I was annoyed because no color options were provided. We put the pieces together. Each piece fits together with a Velcro flap. I got over the color mismatch but I was annoyed because the two pieces didn’t fit together seamlessly. It had a gap. I think this is due to low quality control. Amazon exchanged one half to hopefully remove the unsafe middle gap. It’s a balance beam and a gap in the middle is an injury waiting to happen. I should have known better because if you look closely at the beams in the stock photos look like junk.

Review text: My first issue with this product was that the photos lead you to believe you are ordering a regular size balance beam. Upon arrival I noticed a short box but thought nothing of it. I figured the box contained two pieces that connected to form a full beam. Unfortunately, when my niece opened her gift the box only contained one 4 foot piece. I was scratching my head. Minutes later I fired up the amazon app and bought another to complete the full 8’ beam. The second package arrived 2 days later. My niece was excited. I wasn’t thrilled because the first 4 footer had a blue bottom and the second one arrived with a purple bottom. This wasn’t a huge deal but I was annoyed because no color options were provided. We put the pieces together. Each piece fits together with a Velcro flap. I got over the color mismatch but I was annoyed because the two pieces didn’t fit together seamlessly. It had a gap. I think this is due to low quality control. Amazon exchanged one half to hopefully remove the unsafe middle gap. It’s a balance beam and a gap in the middle is an injury waiting to happen. Furthermore, the plastic bottoms do not have grips so the beam will slide on wood floors. In short, the product is crap. I should have known better because if you look closely at the beams in the stock photos look like junk.

Review text: My first issue with this product was that the photos lead you to believe you are ordering a regular size balance beam. Upon arrival I noticed a short box but thought nothing of it. I figured the box contained two pieces that connected to form a full beam. Unfortunately, when my niece opened her gift the box only contained one 4 foot piece. I was scratching my head. I wasn’t thrilled because the first 4 footer had a blue bottom and the second one arrived with a purple bottom. This wasn’t a huge deal but I was annoyed because no color options were provided. We put the pieces together. Each piece fits together with a Velcro flap. I got over the color mismatch but I was annoyed because the two pieces didn’t fit together seamlessly. It had a gap. I think this is due to low quality control. Amazon exchanged one half to hopefully remove the unsafe middle gap. It’s a balance beam and a gap in the middle is an injury waiting to happen. Furthermore, the plastic bottoms do not have grips so the beam will slide on wood floors. In short, the product is crap. I should have known better because if you look closely at the beams in the stock photos look like junk.

Review text: My 79 year old husband is trying to regain his balance.  This arrived today and we centered it in a narrow hallway.  This way he can touch the walls as he walks it.  It is well made and having it in brown blends in with the floor.  It folds in half and has a strong piece of Velcro to secure the fold while in use.  It has a strong enough foam for my 155 pound husband to feel stable and it’s covered with a soft suede on the top side and a rubber type fabric on the bottom which holds the beam on a wood floor.  It holds even better on carpet but we wanted the hall walls to aid him.  The width and height is like a 2 x 4 board with slanted sides beyond that.  It comes with a nice storage bag.  The beam is so light weight that I can hold it in one hand.  Matter of fact, it was so light that I thought it would never work, but it’s great and the light weight is an asset!  You can store it anywhere! If I could change anything, I wish it was 6 or 7 inches across the top like at physical therapy but theirs was over 100.00! I would buy this again.
